				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$D_{2h}^5$$\end{document}) on an orthorhombic (a, b/2, c) unit-cell basis with zero origin shift relative to the child. We also idealize the FE children by replacing each AMP cation with an appropriate polar vector in order to apply the symmetry mode analysis consistently.

